 for bestpractices and # Edit / Manage Listing

## Overview
Build a contextual, provider-agnostic Edit / Manage Listing page that enables users to edit listing metadata, re-run AI Vision QA checks, view operations notes, and take actions such as resubmitting to review or scheduling an auction. This page sits at the center of a broader intake, enrichment, and QA pipeline and must integrate seamlessly with the AI Vision QA pipeline, the Intake & Enrichment pipeline, and the Connected Pages (notably Create Listing). Ensure runtime safety per the project’s mandatory coding standards, especially guarding against null/undefined values before array operations and initializing React state with the correct defaults.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A comprehensive management interface for a single listing that has been created via the Intake Wizard or imported via the identifier-based flow. It enables the seller or ops user to:
  - Edit and save listing metadata (title, description, category, specs, identifiers, pricing fields, schedule windows, auction settings, etc.).
  - Re-run AI Vision QA checks on the listing’s photos/specs and view the structured QA outputs (hard-fail vs warnings, tags, confidence, evidence images).
  - View a structured Ops Notes panel containing reviewer comments, status, timestamps, and actionable tasks.
  - Resubmit the listing for review or schedule an auction window (and optionally archive or place on hold).
  - Manage listing photos: replace, delete, or reorder; re-run QA for changed photos without re-uploading the entire set.
  - Access a summary of identifier-based enrichment results, including pre-filled specs and any async enrichment status.
  - Trigger related workflows (e.g., trigger further enrichment, kick off compliance/history checks at the correct workflow stage).

Connected features and integrations:
- AI Vision QA Pipeline (Provider-Agnostic): Pluggable pipeline that can start with general vision APIs plus a rule engine and later swap to specialist providers. Outputs a structured JSON QA payload containing:
  - hard-fail indicators, warnings, and tags
  - confidence scores
  - evidence images or image references
  - structured evidence mapping to listing fields
- Intake & Enrichment Pipeline: Async, multi-step enrichment that uses identifier-based input to pre-fill specs; supports drafts and an ability to edit enriched fields before final submission.
- Data flow and permissions: Ensure only authorized ops users or listing owners can edit; use RBAC checks; include audit logging of edits and QA runs.
- No external API endpoints should be assumed as always-on; Centralize API integration points with clear provider-agnostic interfaces and a pluggable architecture.

UI guidance and visual guidance:
- Listing Details Form: Prefilled with existing listing data; fields editable; validation rules applied; changes staged before save.
- Photo Manager: Grid of photos with actions to replace, delete, reorder; a “Re-run AI QA” action that can operate on specific photos or the entire set; show QA results per photo.
- QA Panel: Highlight hard-fail items prominently; show a list of warnings; show tags with confidence; display evidence thumbnails; allow filtering by QA category.
- Ops Notes: Read-only history with latest notes; expandable items for full comments; timestamped entries; status indicators.
- Actions: Clear CTAs for “Resubmit for Review,” “Schedule Auction,” and “Archive Listing.” Use consistent button styles per design system (neon yellow-green CTA, secondary options outlined).
- Feedback and validation: Inline validation cues; success/error toasts or inline messaging with accessible aria-live regions.

UI Elements & UI guidance:
- Use a strict grid layout with generous padding, left-aligned data, and visually grouped sections (Listing Details, Photos & QA, Ops Notes, Actions).
- Cards with soft shadows and rounded corners; hover/active states emphasize interactivity.
- Data visualizations: Minimalist horizontal bars to reflect QA confidence or QA severity; color-coded (green for success, red for errors, neutral for warnings).
- Navigation: Persistent bottom tab bar for app-wide navigation with neon yellow-green accents on active icons.

Visual and design references (per project guidelines):
- Color Palette, Typography, Layout, Card, and Data Visualization guidelines provided.
- All interactive elements must comply with accessible color contrast and keyboard navigation.

API integrations:
- No hard-coded API endpoints are assumed; implement adapters to fetch/update listing data, run QA, fetch enrichment results, fetch and post ops notes, manage photos, and trigger scheduling.
- AI QA outputs must be structured JSON; if an engine returns a different shape, normalize it to the expected schema before rendering.

## Components to Build
- ListingEditForm
  - Props: listing data, onChange, onSave
  - Fields: title, description, category, specs (structured), price, reserve, auctionWindow, identifiers, location, etc.
  - Behavior: Form-level validation; dirty-tracking; autosave stub or manual save; prefill from listing data; guard against null/undefined values when mapping fields.
- PhotosPanel
  - Props: photos[], onReplace( idx ), onDelete( idx ), onReorder, onQAUpdate
  - Features: thumbnail grid, upload/replace, delete, drag-to-reorder (or up/down), per-photo QA results; batch or per-photo QA re-run.
  - Behavior: Ensure photos array is always an array: (photos ?? []).map(...). Guard all array ops with Array.isArray checks or use safe defaults.
- QAResultsPanel
  - Props: qaOutput
  - Display: hierarchy of hard-fail items, warnings, tags, confidence, evidence images/thumbnails; per-item drill-down; filter controls.
  - Behavior: Expandable sections; allow user to navigate to affected fields in ListingEditForm.
- OpsNotesPanel
  - Props: notes[], onAddNote
  - Display: list of notes with status, reviewer, timestamp; ability to view prior decisions; show a summary of open actions.
  - Behavior: Validation for new note entry; immutable history preserved.
- EnrichmentOverview
  - Props: enrichmentResults, status
  - Display: pre-filled specs vs currently edited values; status indicators for enrichment pipeline (pending, partial, complete); async status badges.
- ActionsBar
  - Props: onResubmit, onScheduleAuction, onArchive, isBusy
  - Display: CTA buttons with proper states (disabled while processing); confirmation dialogs for destructive actions.
- IdentifierEnrichmentStatus
  - Props: enrichmentStatus, lastUpdated
  - Display: a compact status line with a quick link to the enrichment results.
- ValidationSummary
  - Props: validationErrors, warnings
  - Display: concise list of issues preventing submission; links to fields in ListingEditForm.
- API Adapters / Hooks
  - useListing, useQA, useEnrichment, usePhotos, useNotes hooks with safe defaults and explicit null/undefined guards.
  - Ensure all data fetched via Supabase-like clients use data ?? [] and Array.isArray guard logic.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Frameworks: Next.js (App Router) with TypeScript.
- State Management: Local component state for forms with useState and useEffect; derived state for QA results; global-ish state via context or simple prop drilling as appropriate.
- Hooks and Guards:
  - Always initialize arrays as useState<Type[]>([]) and never use useState() with an undefined default for arrays.
  - When consuming API results, guard with Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
  - When mapping arrays, use (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
  - Access nested API objects with optional chaining: obj?.property?.nested.
  - Provide default values via destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.
- Form validations: required fields, max lengths, valid formats (URL, price, date/time for scheduling); show inline error messages.
- Performance: lazy load QA results if large; debounce user interactions where appropriate.
- Accessibility: aria attributes for dynamic panels; keyboard navigable; contrast-compliant colors; semantic HTML.
- Responsiveness: layout adapts to tablet/mobile with collapsible panels; maintain visual hierarchy.

### Backend
- APIs and DB schema (Postgres via Supabase):
  - Listings table: id, owner_id, title, description, category, specs JSON, identifiers JSON, pricing, schedule, status, qa_status, qa_results JSON, enrichment_status, enrichment_results JSON, ops_notes_id, photos array/relations, created_at, updated_at, archived boolean, etc.
  - Photos table: id, listing_id, url, order, is_primary, qa_results JSON, created_at, updated_at.
  - QAResults table or field: store provider-agnostic QA outputs as structured JSON per QA run.
  - OpsNotes table: id, listing_id, author_id, note, status, created_at, related_action.
  - Enrichment table: listing_id, status, results JSON, updated_at.
  - Activity log table: id, listing_id, event_type, payload JSON, created_at.
- Functions/Endpoints:
  - GET /listings/{id} — fetch listing with related photos, QA, enrichment, notes.
  - PATCH /listings/{id} — update listing metadata; merge changes; guard against invalid fields; handle optimistic concurrency if needed.
  - POST /listings/{id}/qa/run — trigger AI Vision QA pipeline; accept optional subset of photos; return structured QA results.
  - POST /listings/{id}/qa/handle — save QA results, tag as hard-fail or warning; store evidence references.
  - POST /listings/{id}/enrichment/retry — trigger enrichment pipeline; handle async status updates.
  - POST /listings/{id}/photos/{photoId}/replace — replace a photo; re-run QA as needed.
  - POST /listings/{id}/notes — add an ops note.
  - POST /listings/{id}/schedule — schedule an auction window.
  - POST /listings/{id}/archive — archive listing.
- Security:
  - Implement RBAC: only listing owners, admins, or Ops roles may edit; enforce authorization on each endpoint.
  Use row-level security (RLS) with listing_id guards; audit logs for all mutations.
- Validation:
  - Validate JSON fields (specs, identifiers) with schemas; ensure required fields present on resubmit or schedule; sanitize inputs.

### Integration
- AI Vision QA Pipeline (Provider-Agnostic):
  - Define a pluggable interface:
    - startQa(listingId, photos, inputData) => Promise<{ hardFail: boolean; warnings: string[]; tags: string[]; confidence: number; evidenceImages: string[]; resultsByField?: Record<string, any> }>
  - Allow swap to provider-specific adapters later without changing core UI/UX code.
  - Normalize QA outputs to a standard JSON schema for UI rendering and storage.
- Intake & Enrichment Pipeline:
  - Trigger on initial create or on demand; enrich using listing identifiers; populate prefilled specs; support async status with a callback webhook or polling endpoint.
  - Persist enrichment results; offer user to accept or edit enriched values before resubmission.
- Data flow:
  - Ensure all edits to listing metadata trigger appropriate status transitions (e.g., from Draft -> Pending QA -> Ready for Review).
  - QA results should be timestamped and auditable; if QA fails, prevent resubmission until issues resolved.
- Supabase integration:
  - Use data ?? [] and Array.isArray guards whenever reading results from Supabase queries.
  - Use real-time sync for auctions and status updates if applicable, without breaking the Edit / Manage Listing experience.

## User Experience Flow
1) User opens Edit / Manage Listing for a specific listing.
2) ListingDetailsForm is prefilled with current data; user edits metadata (title, description, specs, pricing, schedule, identifiers, etc.).
3) PhotosPanel shows current photos with ability to replace/delete/reorder; user can re-run QA for individual photos or the entire set.
4) QAResultsPanel displays the latest AI Vision QA results; hard-fail items are highlighted; warnings are listed; evidence images are shown; user can navigate to affected fields in the form.
5) OpsNotesPanel shows past reviewer notes; user can add new notes (if allowed) or review status and actions required.
6) EnrichmentOverview shows any pending/completed enrichment results; user can accept enriched values or edit them.
7) ActionsBar provides CTAs:
   - Resubmit for Review (validate required fields and QA status)
   - Schedule Auction (open a modal/date picker; validate schedule window)
   - Archive Listing (with confirmation)
8) On Save or Resubmit, backend validates inputs, triggers necessary pipelines (QA, enrichment), and updates statuses; UI shows progress indicators and success/error messages.
9) If the listing moves to an Auction schedule, the Auction Engine will take over at the connected queue.

## Technical Specifications

### Data Models
- Listings
  - id (UUID)
  - owner_id (FK to Users)
  - title (string)
  - description (text)
  - category (string)
  - specs (JSON)
  - identifiers (JSON)
  - price (numeric)
  - reserve_price (numeric)
  - auction_window (timestamptz or JSON window)
  - qa_status (string: Draft | InProgress | Failed | Passed | NeedsRework)
  - qa_results (JSON)
  - enrichment_status (string: Pending | Complete | Failed)
  - enrichment_results (JSON)
  - status (string: Draft | Pending QA | Ready for Review | Scheduled | Archived)
  - photos (array of Photo records or separate Photos table)
  - ops_notes_id (FK)
  - created_at, updated_at, archived
- Photos
  - id (UUID)
  - listing_id (FK)
  - url (string)
  - order (int)
  - is_primary (boolean)
  - qa_results (JSON)
  - created_at, updated_at
- OpsNotes
  - id (UUID)
  - listing_id (FK)
  - author_id (FK to Users)
  - note (text)
  - status (string)
  - created_at
- Enrichment
  - id (UUID)
  - listing_id (FK)
  - status (Pending | Complete | Failed)
  - results (JSON)
  - updated_at
- ActivityLog
  - id
  - listing_id
  - event_type
  - payload (JSON)
  - created_at

### API Endpoints (Routes and Methods)
- GET /api/listings/{id}
- PATCH /api/listings/{id}
- POST /api/listings/{id}/qa/run
- POST /api/listings/{id}/qa/update
- POST /api/listings/{id}/photos/{photoId}/replace
- POST /api/listings/{id}/notes
- POST /api/listings/{id}/enrichment/retry
- POST /api/listings/{id}/schedule
- POST /api/listings/{id}/archive
- GET /api/listings/{id}/qa/history (optional audit trail)
- GET /api/enrichment/{listingId}
- Webhook handlers for external QA/enrichment providers (idempotent)

### Security
- Authentication: JWT/OAuth session with role-based access control.
- Authorization: RBAC to ensure only owners or admins can edit; restrict QA runs to authorized roles.
- Data protection: sanitize all inputs; store sensitive data securely; follow least-privilege principle.
- Auditability: store all edits, QA runs, and status changes in ActivityLog; include user, action, timestamp.

### Validation
- Frontend:
  - Required fields: title, at least one photo, valid schedule if scheduling, price, category.
  - Descriptive inline validation messages and field-level validation rules.
  - Use consistent date validation for scheduling.
  - Guard all array accesses with (array ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(array) ? array.map(...) : [].
- Backend:
  - Validate input payloads with schema validation; throw 400 on invalid shapes.
  - Ensure listingId matches authenticated user’s scope.
  - Validate that QA results originate from a known provider interface or normalized schema.
  - Idempotent handling for webhooks and QA re-runs.

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The Edit / Manage Listing page renders with all sections: Listing Details, Photos, QA Results, Ops Notes, Enrichment Overview, and Actions.
- [ ] All array operations in frontend code guard against null/undefined by using nullish coalescing and Array.isArray guards; use useState<Type[]>([]) defaults for all array state.
- [ ] Re-run QA button triggers provider-agnostic QA pipeline; QA results normalize to a consistent JSON schema and are stored in listing.qa_results.
- [ ] Enrichment results are displayed; unfilled fields are pre-filled and editable; enrichment can be retried, and status updates reflect in the UI.
- [ ] Submitting for review validates required fields; if QA has hard-fail, submission is blocked with actionable messages.
- [ ] Scheduling an auction validates date/time windows and updates listing status to Scheduled; the Auction Engine must receive scheduling payload.
- [ ] All actions audit with ActivityLog; unauthorized actions are blocked with proper error messaging.

